author: @opokusm
text: The main reason models don't detect distant objects is because all of them have relatively small input resolution (usually 300X300 pixels) and whatever resolution input you pass, it gets automatically resized to this input shape, losing a lot of details needed to detect objects. Also game world is slightly different from real world and that is enough for weaker (and because of that faster) models to fail to generalize to the way cars, and other objects of interest, look in GTAV world and as a result fail to detect them. I would advice to try transfer learning with around half of training data consisting of random frames taken from game, there is no need to label them by hand, simply take the most accurate model from object detection api and use its predictions, should be more than enough to train better fast model. Reducing amount of classes to predict, also helps small models to reach better accuracy.
